HEADWORD: Secularization
<hw>Sec`u*lar*i*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧cularisation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of rendering
secular, or the state of being rendered secular; conversion from regular
or monastic to secular; conversion from religious to lay or secular
possession and uses; <as>as, the <ex>secularization</ex> of church
property</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

